description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_dropline-slow.wav
tags: alien button clack click electro hi-tech mutate processing robot soundesign switch transform cyborg cuts soundeffect digital effect noise fx glitch slices

description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_dropline-fast.wav
tags: off button clack click cyborg transform electro hi-tech mutate processing robot soundesign switch alien digital effect cuts fx glitch slices soundeffect noise

description:
Zip twisting mechanism sound, then a drop glug sound. Also sound like a bottle glug.

USE EXAMPLES: You can use this in a number of ways if you edit it.

1. Parking meter.
2. Edit/cut the sound so that it sounds like you are using a drink vending machine. 
3. Use the end glug sound as bottle being put down. Or copy and past the glug multiple times in a row to simulate someone heavily drinking from a bottle.
4. Glug sound can be used as something dropping in water.

-[ RECORDING INFO ]-

I created this accidentally while making bead strand zip sounds and hitting the microphone. 

STUDIO MIC: AT4033
RECORDED IN: Adobe Audition 3
MASTERED: Using EQ, Compressed, Noise Gated, and Normalized to -.1

*NO CREDIT IS EVER NEEDED TO USE MY SAMPLES!
*Read my profile for further info.
name: Change-Drink-Machine-Beads-Pulled_by-JGrimm.wav
tags: change coke drink machine meter parking vending

description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_click.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:38.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/38.0
description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_rim2.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_rim2.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

description: The sound of the packing machine at the Freia chocolate and powdered dessert factory in Oslo. This machine filled powder into small consumer packages, ready for easy-made puddings and jelly dessert. The end product is still available and something of an icon in Norway. The machine on this soundbit was swiss made, measured about 10 by 10 meters, and was substituted for s smaller in 2002. The Norwegian Museum of Science, technology and industry in Oslo documented the machine before it was dismanteled.
name: freiamaskin_loop.WAV
tags: dessert factory freia industry kraft-foods machine oslo packing-machine pudding

This machine filled powder into small consumer packages, ready for easy-made puddings and jelly dessert. The end product is still available and something of an icon in Norway. The machine on this soundbit was swiss made, measured about 10 by 10 meters, and was substituted for s smaller in 2002. The Norwegian Museum of Science, technology and industry in Oslo documented the machine before it was dismanteled.
name: freiamaskin_loop.WAV
tags: dessert factory freia industry kraft-foods machine oslo packing-machine pudding
